                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">ff. 1v-2</locus>
                           <desc>r: Malkǝʾa beta krǝstiyān “Image of the Church”.  </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: ሰላም፡ ለኪ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ሎዛ፡ ቤተ፡ ያዕቆብ፡
                              ወሬዛ፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The image is incomplete (apparently, only the beginning) and very
                              crudely written. It is not registered in ChRep. The end part of the
                              poem mentions Näʾakkʷǝto Läʾab, ʾEfrem, Gabra Māryām and Lalibäla who
                              are asked “to protect their sheep from the lion’s mouth”. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work, ዳዊት፡, is written on a white piece
                           of paper glued on the front cover.
 - The midpoint of the “Psalms of
                           David” (in P<locus target="#77">77</locus>) is marked on <locus target="#60v">60v</locus> with a sign ዝየ written in the inner
                           margin.
 - The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated by a
                           line of alternating black and red dots or by an ornamental band. 
 -
                           The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the whole
                           line or the end of the line: e.g., <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>, 10r,
                           24v, 26r, 45r, 51v, 72v, 81r.
 - Part of the line is taken up: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#4v">4v</locus>, 18r.
 - Part of the line is taken
                           down: <locus target="#107r">107r</locus>.
 - Tamallas-sign, in the
                           shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the
                           omission, written in the upper margin, belongs: <locus target="#9v">9v</locus> l.15.
 - Omitted letters, words, lines or passages
                           written interlineally, in the main hand: e.g., <locus target="#4v">4v</locus>, 8r, 19r, 46v, 54r, 74v, 75v, 80v, 131r.
 - Scribbles,
                           doodles: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 2v, 36r, 88r, 124v, 138v, 143v,
                           144rv, 145rv.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Daily readings are indicated by the names of days of
                              the week crudely written in the upper margin of fols. 23v, 23r, 46v,
                              64v, 87v, 88r, 91v, 92r, 101v, 102r, 113v, 114r.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
